{"source_hash": "c369785ca23ca159", "candidate": {"id": "cand-001", "name": "Priya Sharma", "raw_cv": "PRIYA SHARMA\npriya.sharma@email.com | LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/priyasharma-de | London, UK\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 6 years of experience building production data pipelines in regulated financial environments. Specialist in Python, SQL, dbt, and Snowflake. Proven track record delivering low-latency data products for trading and payments teams.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Data Engineer \u2014 Barclays Corporate & Investment Bank, London (2021\u2013present)\n- Designed and owned the trade reconciliation pipeline processing 500k+ events/day using Python and Kafka\n- Migrated 40+ legacy ETL jobs to dbt + Airflow, reducing maintenance overhead by 60%\n- Introduced Great Expectations for data quality validation across the data warehouse (Snowflake)\n- Mentored 2 junior engineers; led sprint planning for a team of 5\n\nData Engineer \u2014 GoCardless, London (2019\u20132021)\n- Built and maintained real-time payment reconciliation pipelines using Python and BigQuery\n- Developed internal dbt models for financial reporting used by the CFO function\n- Collaborated with data science team to productionise fraud detection features\n\nJunior Data Engineer \u2014 Accenture, London (2018\u20132019)\n- Delivered SQL-based ETL pipelines for a retail banking client migration project\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, dbt, Snowflake, BigQuery, Apache Airflow, Apache Kafka, Great Expectations, Spark (basic), Git, Docker\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 University of Edinburgh (2015\u20132018)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "I'm a data engineer with six years in fintech and payments, specialising in building reliable data infrastructure that finance teams can actually trust. Currently at Barclays CIB, where I lead pipeline engineering for the trade operations data platform. I've spent most of my career in Python and SQL, with a strong focus on dbt and Snowflake. Before Barclays I was at GoCardless helping scale their data platform during a period of rapid growth. I care deeply about data quality \u2014 if the numbers aren't right, nothing downstream matters. I'm based in London and open to senior data engineering roles, ideally in a fast-paced financial or fintech environment.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Thanks for coming in, Priya. Can you start by telling me a bit about your current role?\n\nPriya: Sure. I'm a senior data engineer at Barclays CIB. My main focus is the trade reconciliation platform \u2014 we process around half a million events a day and latency is critical. I own the pipeline architecture end-to-end, from Kafka ingestion through to Snowflake and the dbt models that feed the reconciliation dashboards.\n\nInterviewer: What draws you to this role specifically?\n\nPriya: A few things. I've been at Barclays for nearly four years now and I'm ready for a new challenge in a smaller, faster-moving environment. Apex's payments infrastructure focus is really aligned with what I've been doing. I want to stay in fintech.\n\nInterviewer: How do you feel about the onsite requirement? We're five days a week in Canary Wharf.\n\nPriya: That works perfectly for me. I actually prefer being in the office \u2014 I find I collaborate better in person, and for a role like this where you're working closely with quant analysts, being present matters. I live in Bethnal Green so the commute is easy.\n\nInterviewer: Great. And salary expectations?\n\nPriya: I'm currently on \u00a378,000 and I'm looking for something in the \u00a382\u201387,000 range depending on the full package.\n\nInterviewer: Do you have any questions for us?\n\nPriya: Yes \u2014 what does the on-call rotation look like for the data platform team?", "years_experience": 6.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "BigQuery", "Apache Airflow", "Apache Kafka", "Great Expectations", "Spark", "Git", "Docker"], "industries": ["fintech", "financial services", "payments"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.87, "culture_fit_score": 0.84, "constraints": [{"id": "1325a4d5", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a378,000 (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 78000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "b35d61c6", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum \u00a382,000 in new role (interview stated \u00a382\u201387k range)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "c68e0386", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation range \u00a382\u201387,000 (interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 87000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "eda44df5", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Prefers full-time in-office work; stated 5 days per week in Canary Wharf works perfectly", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 5.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93}, {"id": "8aa259c3", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Based in London (Bethnal Green); committed to London-based roles", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "London", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97}, {"id": "31d26e91", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "British citizen; visa sponsorship not required", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": false, "operator": "excludes", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "30b811ac", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_environment", "description"